solution: ```class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLongestSubstring(String s) {
        int[] last = new int[256];
        for (int i = 0; i < 256; i++) last[i] = -1;
        int left = 0, max = 0;
        for (int right = 0; right < s.length(); right++) {
            char c = s.charAt(right);
            if (last[c] >= left) left = last[c] + 1;
            last[c] = right;
            max = Math.max(max, right - left + 1);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sliding-window with a fixed-size array to store the last index of each character. The window expands rightward and contracts leftward only when a duplicate is found, guaranteeing each character is processed at most twice.

